 wish you wouldn't go, and I said, well, I'm glad - we're glad of the money, that woman, she - I used to go - about nine o'clock and she used to give me a bit of dinner and she - I used to get home about six o'clock in the evening for me tea. But you see,
 we were glad of the money 'cos we was a family never to get into debt.
