xt morning and saw this man at the building society, and my brother - in-law - at Norwich, they had no family, got a good job, he lent us some money, and we paid twelve pound deposit - the price was a hundred and twenty. Pound - but we couldn't get the pe
o
ple out. This old Major Berkley, we used to come every week and he said - you must go to court. I said, Major Bartlett - I said - I shall not go to court - if I did I should lose a day, I said, and I try to live a straight life and I wouldn't do such a th
ing to a widow woman, I said, with a son in the army. Oh he was an old rascal And - that was so heavily mortgaged that the deeds had to go to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}France{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} one of the mortgagees lived out there that we never got the deeds 'til - the following March. And then old Major Bartlett come one day and he said, oh, he said - I've come to to tell you that Mrs Rand, he said, I - I didn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6773215\charrsid8475667 adjudicate}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10314666\charrsid8475667 
 at the meeting he said, but they've allowed Mrs Rand to have a council cottage 'til let on Framley Lane. How soon can you can get
 out? I said I don't know. And - so they got out. And they took the board away with 'em. Which they'd no business to have done, and - of course that wanted a lot of doing to, and - one or two helped me brothers, got it papered and done it all out, and he 
come down and he said, when you going to move, I'd had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6773215\charrsid8475667 abscess}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10314666\charrsid8475667 
 in both sides of me so Mrs Jackson want's to move in he said, her daughters are coming I said well I've got nobody to help me, I'd had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6773215\charrsid8475667 abscess}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10314666\charrsid8475667  each side of me face so you can guess I felt a bit 
- and so I said - I shall move when I'm ready. I said, it wants a new fireplace, 'cos this woman what bought it she said to me I want a new fire place, oh I'm very sorry but you can't have it. I said, I'll tell my brother you see 'cos he used to do grates
 
and he went and tinkered it up, and do you know when my - we moved she pulled the bedroom fireplace right out. Spiteful you see. 'Cos - when me brother come home from Waldon her son gone in to buy it. She told people it was over run with rats when they - 
went to look at it, but of course we had to fill the - big pantry in with chalk and all like that, we do - every little - pound or two I got was spent on doing it. And we lived there thirty-three years.
