No. Oh he never have managed. I'll tell you what, in the harvest time - he used to have a four and a half gallon cask from brewery at Radwinter - for his - summer drink, and in the harvest time - they used to - when
 - of course I was looking after the home I - used to have to take his dinner, and his - tea you see and then he'd have a - a - something to eat when he come home and the sun was so hot that time of day - his arms was as brown as a berry. Well we - we don
'
t have the summers. I mean - look at - over the station there's a - there's - marshy piece of ground that was always flooded for skating and Pond Cross far there's a - there - there used to be a pond in the yard and people used to skate on that, well you 
don't - well my niece Elsie was - grown up and out teaching when she first saw skating at Debden Park.
