her but the wonderful mother. My father was a good man. And I always think that's perfectly true - that what you put into life - if you live to get old - older you get out - you get - what you get is good out of it 'cos I find that's true. My mother put a
 
lot into her life for her family and - though I was the chief one what done it she never wanted for anything. All - I mean she was in bed a couple of years except getting her out at night and - I can truly say I had a good father and a wonderful mother, s
h
e was - and she always used to say - the happiest time of her life was when her children was round her. And when you see me father never come home 'til six o'clock at night and we used to sit in the firelight when we come out of school, and she - we used 
