 peel and she used to make a very large Christmas pudding and put it in a big square cloth. And tie it up and put - when she cooked for us on Sunday there was a big iron boiler. And - she kept it - boiling all night, used to get up and make the - and make
 
the fire up and so there was a lovely - pudding, and every Christmas Eve we used to come down to this old grammar school 'cos there was a lot of - of greenery there after decorating the church from Shelgrove, and - you could always take home a piece for a
 
