e used to put two shillings to whatever you paid in she used to negotiate with Barnes Brothers - and we used to get a ton of coal for seventeen shillings, well that was all right for the winter. You see, I don't know what is in that book 'cos there's no -
 
I've never got anybody to read it to me. They haven't got time to read. And the doctor's orders, so I'm going to see you've autographed that book. I said, you know I haven't got anybody - oh he said, I'll come. I said certainly not. Well I shall find some
