\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16153212 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10314666\charrsid8475667 
Well - that would be your schoolmaster - and - and the vicar, and curate. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6762071 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10314666\charrsid8475667 W
ho did the tradespeople mix with in their sort of social life, who would they have to their house for tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16153212 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10314666\charrsid8475667 
Well they saw - when we had a choir tea and - and - in the war, concerts or anything we sort of all mixed together, that altered things the second world war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6762071 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10314666\charrsid8475667 
I'm wanting to try and find out how it was before the end of the first world war, thinking of that time, how they different classes were, how they behave with each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16153212 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10314666\charrsid8475667 Well we all sort of all mixed together because - we always 
had a big flower show every year and the - the last one we had was at Shelgrove. And they give the prizes away, and Sir Karl Myer give the prizes away, and he said - it was - he was afraid - it would be the last social gathering, because war was coming. A
n
d that was - well that would be - generally had the flower show the end of July and that was a few days afterwards, and do you know it - he was a German banker they said, - lost his - he died - he - he didn't live to leave there. And of course they kept a
 great many servants up there you see and the gardeners and the boffey and all like of that. And of course that was all done away with as you might say in a moment of days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6762071 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10314666\charrsid8475667 
All very friendly and - one thing always ready to do anything for each other then. No one ever thought of - of - getting anybody in to do the washing when - a baby was born or anything, a neighbour always done it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16153212 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10314666\charrsid8475667 Do you remember what happened when your youngest brother was born.
