Well they were they 'til they finished their training, they were there several months, they was there one - and then it - the second lot we had from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Stafford{\*\xmlclose}
 - shire, and they went abroad and then we had a Scotch - regiment but they wasn't so good 'cos they used to drink so. They all in turn went to fight. That was the first world war.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6762071 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10314666\charrsid8475667 Did they come home drunk then?
