Well - I don't know about drunk but they used to drink a lot, they was a - a lot with these like and then - after I
 time, I don't know, I - we - well I don't think we - we had 'em quite 'til the end of the war but we had 'em - long time. Well I had the first I had was a Welshman and a Scotchman and a - young man eighteen from - Waltham Abbey which is in Essex and one 
f
rom - Cornwall or Devon, he was a schoolteacher. But the chemist was a very superior man, and after - the war he caught a chill playing golf and died of blood poisoning, he used to come and see me and - and his brother came - on the way to Cambridge. And 
-
 and he used to look after this young Andy, he was only eighteen. They went out in the desert and used to - one sent me a lovely rosary and a cross on - another one the stamp box I've got there from Jerusalem. And I helped 'em all I could. Well that was -
 I mean they - yes.
