Well - I don't know if we was brought up to it but I always used to - to fight back. Because I remember an incident that - a woman gave me 
a little armchair to sit in and the boy came and take it - took it away, and I took it from him and punched him, and this woman said to my mother, she said, oh your daughter is - is a little spitfire. Well, my mother said, it was given to her. And I kept 
t
he chair. But anyway I was only very small, and my - mother has reminded me of that, but I can remember it plainly. You see, the boy took this and I think she was moving house, took this little chair away from me. And that's the only time else otherwise -
 
if girls used to - sometimes - talk about my clothes, was always tidy but they was never smart, 'cos I told you before clothes was a problem, with the three boys 'cos mother used to make their trousers if she could get anything to make 'em with, but I use
d to just feel hurt about it. I never -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid6762071 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10314666\charrsid8475667 Said anything to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16153212 MR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10314666\charrsid8475667 
No, no, I was always - well, matter of fact I was always rather a nervous child really. Mm.
