Oh yes, I should think I might have been - seven or eight, she was paralyzed and lived with her daughter and died and I don't think mother knew - but I went down - when 
I come out of school to see her in her coffin. And she lay there, it was the time of year when violets was out, oh this does stand out in my memory, and she'd got some violets - lay in her hand, and I said to my Aunt Fanny, they said - well - well - will 
