I can't remember that. It was the Liberal people got in then, it was a Mr Pease, he was a Liberal man, he wasn't a bad sort. And then there was another man, I suppose he was sort of a Labour man, Joseph Arch, come round and told the people ev
ery man should have three acres and a cow. I - I - I remember my parents talking about it but I can't remember it - what he was like or anything, but they - mother used to say you know it was all rubbish, it couldn't come to pass well it never has and nev
er will. No. I've always been interested in - and -
\par 
